<br>
1-4: Any newbie area. I used Prendwyn(sp?) Keep mostly.<br>
<br>
5-8: Bandit area North of the bridge to West Downs.<br>
<br>
9-14: Salisbury Plains along the road opposite West Downs. Also in the Northern half of Campo Forest.<br>
<br>
15 - 18: Avalon Marsh, across the bridge from Adribard's Retreat on the Cornwall side of the river. Ghouls are excellent experience and loot for this level range in a full group.<br>
<br>
19 - 22: Cornwall. Start with undead Romans, then cliff spiders moving up to Cornish Hunters, elder beeches and finally (at about level 22 at the earliest) rooters at the hog farm.<br>
<br>
Other good spots I found, but can't remember at what levels I hunted there: Snowdonia, Llyn Barfog (this was in the late teens and the area was too difficult for us at that level), Suavage Forest (RvR area, so heads up, but also good hunting in the early 20's). I didn't use any of the dungeons for experience hunting, but they are great experience as well. From what I've seen (I hunted three dungeons in Albion) you're always better off with a full group in a dungeon.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps!<br>
<br>
Dog<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Big Boss</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/8/01 8:41:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwinclients.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Albion Hunting Guide</span><hr size=1> 1-4: You can solo these levels, and I suggest you spend about 1/4 of your time doing quests and tasks for exp. at this level. <br>
5-8: Bandit areas are good, especially in small groups. At 8th you can do the entrance to Mitrhas' Tomb (in Camelot Hills) with a group. Do not try to do the Demon Ruins in Camelot Hills (close to the bridge to Salisbury Plains) solo before 9, and I'd suggest a group always. <br>
9-10: Filidh camps in Salisbury Plains, West Downs area (across the road) Boulderlings to the east of the Salisbury Plains bridge, Demon Ruins. Keep in mind all of these areas are best in a group due to the fact that some named spawns in these areas are bad chain aggro pulls. Also, tomb raiders in Salisbury Plains are good, but make sure you have a range puller (Scout, Infiltrator are best). <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bdaggersincamelot.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=belce>Belce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/8/01 10:38:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Albion Hunting Guide</span><hr size=1> Actually casters are good to pull with. <br>
<br>
Cleric pulls with stun, no damage low aggro, no call for help.<br>
<br>
Scout pulls with bow, does critical, big damage = big aggro<br>
<br>
Armsman pulls with crossbow, short range means taking some hits on the way back = healing induced aggro. <br>
<br>
Low or no damage spells are good to pull with since aggro is not a problem and range is good.  MOB's will not do their call for help thing as well. <br>
